Activate virtual env : source venv/bin/activate
Start server : python slack_bot.py
Check if server is running by going to this URL http://127.0.0.1:3000/

https://slack.com/oauth/v2/authorize?client_id=7855184757495.7892528086800&scope=chat:write,channels:read,groups:read&redirect_uri=https://ripe-rooms-own.loca.lt/oauth/callback

Steps :
Start slack bot : python3 slack_bot.py
Check port 3000:  lsof -i :3000 #checks what is running on port 3000
Get localtunnel url : lt --port 3000 #Get the URL
Add url in request, redirect and get ouath authorization link, click allow and put password. 
Control c and start slack bot : python3 slack_bot.py
Type hello in slack, mention the chatbot.
